    <briefdescription>
<para>A number of BGL and CGAL algorithms require the graph to have (initialized) integer-like indices for its vertices, edges, or faces. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>However, not all graphs intrinsically offer a natural way to attach a unique ID to each element. The following classes and functions paliate this by attaching and initializing external IDs to the elements of the graph. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
